            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". But as a president with a depressed economy and a potential Republican Senate, undoing his own legacy and canceling student debt may be one of Biden’s only options to stimulate the economy — and Democrats argue that he has the power to do it all on his own, whether Senate GOP leader Mitch McConnell likes it or not.",
